meta {
  name: Save User Onboarding Data
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

post {
  url: {{host}}/accounts/onboarding/
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "role": "Data Scientist",
    "goals": [
      "Evaluations",
      "LLM Observability",
      "Uptime monitoring"
    ]
  }
}

docs {
  # Save User Onboarding Data

  Save user's selected role and goals from the onboarding screens.

  ## Request Body

  ```json
  {
    "role": "string",       // Required - Can be predefined or custom role
    "goals": ["string"]     // Required - Array of goals (can be empty)
  }
  ```

  ## Predefined Roles
  - Data Scientist
  - ML Engineer
  - Subject matter expert
  - Product Manager
  - Business Manager
  - (Any custom text is also accepted)

  ## Available Goals
  - Uptime monitoring
  - LLM Observability
  - Evaluations
  - Agent Simulation
  - Prompt Management
  - Data Annotation

  ## Response

  ```json
  {
    "success": true,
    "data": {
      "message": "Onboarding data saved successfully",
      "data": {
        "role": "Data Scientist",
        "goals": ["Evaluations", "LLM Observability", "Uptime monitoring"]
      }
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Validation Errors

  ```json
  {
    "success": false,
    "error": {
      "role": ["Role is required"]
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Empty Goals Example

  Empty goals array is allowed:

  ```json
  {
    "role": "Data Scientist",
    "goals": []
  }
  ```

  ## Notes

  - Requires authentication
  - Role is required (cannot be empty)
  - Goals array is required but can be empty
  - Role is saved directly to user.role field
  - Goals are saved as JSON array to user.goals field
  - Duplicates in goals array are automatically removed
  - Custom roles are supported - just enter any text
  - Data is also tracked in Mixpanel for analytics
}
